 BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO THE Police in Osun State, on Thursday, arraigned a 52 year-old father of three, Bejide Ayodele, for allegedly locking-up his wife and children in their house with padlocks. The Prosecutor, Sergeant Saheed Anifowose, told the court that the defendant committed the offence between September 17 and 18, 2020 around 4:50 pm in House E3, Road 22, OAU Senior Staff Quarters, Ile-Ife. Anifowose said the defendant intimidated his children – Mary Lawance, Ayoowuro Bejide and Tobiloba Bejide – by injuring them in their home. According to him, the defendant conducted himself in a manner likely to cause the breach of peace. Anifowose argued that the offence contravened sections 81, 86 and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Osun, 2002. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the three-count charge of threat with violence, intimidation and breach of peace slammed against him. The defence counsel, Temitope Olajolo, applied for bail for Bejide. Magistrate A. A. Adebayo granted his bail in the sum of N500,000 with one surety in like sum. The case was adjourned till January 1, 2021 for mention.  